  "text": "Any UTP theory has to clearly define its alphabet, that is, the set of observational variables that define its domain of discourse. The theory presented here is inspired by UTPP [CITATION_1] and uses some of the observations presented there: the values associated with all (shared) variables are not mentioned individually, but instead are lumped together; and we assume that all actions are labelled and that we can observe the set of labels that are considered to be \"active\".",
  "correct_citation": {
